WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Hi, it's James here
from "Food Matters,"

00:00:01.470 --> 00:00:04.019 align:middle line:84%
and I wanted to introduce this
special interview that I have

00:00:04.019 --> 00:00:05.340 align:middle line:90%
with Douglas Doman.

00:00:05.340 --> 00:00:06.990 align:middle line:84%
Douglas is the son
of Glenn Doman,

00:00:06.990 --> 00:00:09.810 align:middle line:84%
and Glenn is the founder of The
Institutes for the Achievement

00:00:09.810 --> 00:00:10.950 align:middle line:90%
of Human Potential.

00:00:10.950 --> 00:00:13.890 align:middle line:84%
This is a fantastic
organization in the US

00:00:13.890 --> 00:00:15.780 align:middle line:84%
that helps children
in particular

00:00:15.780 --> 00:00:19.000 align:middle line:84%
who are brain-injured
redevelop function in the body.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.450 align:middle line:84%
And it's breaking research
that they're doing there

00:00:21.450 --> 00:00:24.990 align:middle line:84%
around food, nutrition,
cognitive exercises in order

00:00:24.990 --> 00:00:28.680 align:middle line:84%
to be able to rewire the
brain, and really acknowledges

00:00:28.680 --> 00:00:31.830 align:middle line:84%
this idea of neuroplasticity,
that you can learn and grow

00:00:31.830 --> 00:00:35.490 align:middle line:84%
at any stage of life regardless
of whether you have any brain

00:00:35.490 --> 00:00:38.682 align:middle line:84%
injury, whether it's
cerebral palsy, or autism,

00:00:38.682 --> 00:00:40.890 align:middle line:84%
or if you're on the spectrum,
or if you have dementia

00:00:40.890 --> 00:00:43.050 align:middle line:84%
or Alzheimer's, even
if you're older,

00:00:43.050 --> 00:00:44.850 align:middle line:84%
at any point of
your life, you have

00:00:44.850 --> 00:00:46.680 align:middle line:84%
the capability and
the opportunity,

00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:48.960 align:middle line:84%
leveraging this concept
of neuroplasticity,

00:00:48.960 --> 00:00:51.930 align:middle line:84%
to improve cognitive function,
to improve brain function,

00:00:51.930 --> 00:00:54.030 align:middle line:84%
even if you suffer from
a bit of memory loss.

00:00:54.030 --> 00:00:55.140 align:middle line:84%
Make sure to check
this interview out.

00:00:55.140 --> 00:00:55.800 align:middle line:90%
It's fantastic.

00:00:55.800 --> 00:00:58.175 align:middle line:84%
And especially if you have
kids, this is super important.

00:00:58.175 --> 00:01:00.984 align:middle line:90%
[LIGHT MUSIC]

00:01:00.984 --> 00:01:08.400 align:middle line:90%


00:01:08.400 --> 00:01:14.575 align:middle line:84%
>> When I was two, my father
sold his house and bought

00:01:14.575 --> 00:01:16.950 align:middle line:84%
the campus of The Institutes
for the Achievement of Human

00:01:16.950 --> 00:01:17.880 align:middle line:90%
Potential.

00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:21.510 align:middle line:84%
His house was a small
part of a large donation

00:01:21.510 --> 00:01:24.570 align:middle line:90%
to actually purchase the campus.

00:01:24.570 --> 00:01:27.840 align:middle line:84%
And when The
Institutes started, he

00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:31.590 align:middle line:84%
was just working around
the clock nonstop.

00:01:31.590 --> 00:01:34.620 align:middle line:84%
And my mother was
the head nurse.

00:01:34.620 --> 00:01:39.090 align:middle line:84%
And she was working
around the clock nonstop.

00:01:39.090 --> 00:01:42.120 align:middle line:90%
So my brother and my sister--

00:01:42.120 --> 00:01:45.617 align:middle line:84%
and this was a
surprise for them,

00:01:45.617 --> 00:01:47.700 align:middle line:84%
because they had been used
to having their parents

00:01:47.700 --> 00:01:50.160 align:middle line:90%
all the time--

00:01:50.160 --> 00:01:53.970 align:middle line:90%
I was put off with a nanny.

00:01:53.970 --> 00:01:58.350 align:middle line:84%
But actually, to have
my own full-time adult

00:01:58.350 --> 00:02:02.340 align:middle line:84%
to do what I wanted, and
play, and do everything

00:02:02.340 --> 00:02:04.770 align:middle line:84%
was just a wonderful
life for me.

00:02:04.770 --> 00:02:08.280 align:middle line:84%
And my father, to
make up for the fact

00:02:08.280 --> 00:02:13.200 align:middle line:84%
that he was working so
hard, permitted the children

00:02:13.200 --> 00:02:17.700 align:middle line:84%
to be with him whenever
he was working anywhere.

00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:19.350 align:middle line:84%
And so we would
sit-in with him when

00:02:19.350 --> 00:02:23.190 align:middle line:84%
he was seeing the parents
of brain-injured children.

00:02:23.190 --> 00:02:27.150 align:middle line:90%
And he had a very strict rule.

00:02:27.150 --> 00:02:30.210 align:middle line:84%
And the rule was, you're welcome
to sit with me in the office,

00:02:30.210 --> 00:02:36.270 align:middle line:84%
be a part of this whole process,
but if we became a distraction,

00:02:36.270 --> 00:02:41.560 align:middle line:84%
he would say, don't go
away mad, just go away.

00:02:41.560 --> 00:02:43.530 align:middle line:84%
And of course, I
would go away mad.

00:02:43.530 --> 00:02:45.940 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

00:02:45.940 --> 00:02:50.920 align:middle line:84%
But when he had wonderful
people coming into the home--

00:02:50.920 --> 00:02:54.730 align:middle line:84%
medical doctors who understood
our work, scientists

00:02:54.730 --> 00:02:56.060 align:middle line:90%
who understood our work--

00:02:56.060 --> 00:02:58.600 align:middle line:84%
we were always
invited to be there.

00:02:58.600 --> 00:03:02.290 align:middle line:84%
And so we just grew up
seeing and understanding

00:03:02.290 --> 00:03:04.330 align:middle line:84%
what was going on
with The Institutes.

00:03:04.330 --> 00:03:06.550 align:middle line:90%
And so we lived there.

00:03:06.550 --> 00:03:07.910 align:middle line:90%
It was a part of our work.

00:03:07.910 --> 00:03:10.778 align:middle line:90%
[LIGHT MUSIC]

00:03:10.778 --> 00:03:13.650 align:middle line:90%


00:03:13.650 --> 00:03:17.960 align:middle line:84%
A huge part of the problem
of what the world calls

00:03:17.960 --> 00:03:22.340 align:middle line:84%
special needs children
is that the diagnosis

00:03:22.340 --> 00:03:25.290 align:middle line:90%
is absolutely chaotic.

00:03:25.290 --> 00:03:28.240 align:middle line:84%
And so there are children
who have cerebral palsy.

00:03:28.240 --> 00:03:30.412 align:middle line:84%
There are children who
are called autistic.

00:03:30.412 --> 00:03:32.120 align:middle line:84%
There are children
who are Down syndrome.

00:03:32.120 --> 00:03:33.980 align:middle line:84%
There are children
who are epileptic.

00:03:33.980 --> 00:03:36.380 align:middle line:84%
There are children that
have learning problems.

00:03:36.380 --> 00:03:39.240 align:middle line:84%
There are children
who are hyperactive.

00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:43.160 align:middle line:84%
And then there is the whole
host of ADHD and all the letters

00:03:43.160 --> 00:03:44.510 align:middle line:90%
that they've created.

00:03:44.510 --> 00:03:47.840 align:middle line:84%
And The Institutes'
now in our 61st year.

00:03:47.840 --> 00:03:51.710 align:middle line:84%
We have seen these
diseases get created.

00:03:51.710 --> 00:03:55.280 align:middle line:84%
And they have just
created more chaos

00:03:55.280 --> 00:03:58.460 align:middle line:84%
from the standpoint of parents
who, when they find out

00:03:58.460 --> 00:04:00.530 align:middle line:84%
they have this kind
of a child, whatever

00:04:00.530 --> 00:04:03.680 align:middle line:84%
label you want to put them in,
they're desperate to find out

00:04:03.680 --> 00:04:05.040 align:middle line:90%
what to do.

00:04:05.040 --> 00:04:09.080 align:middle line:84%
And the problem in the world
of conventional therapy

00:04:09.080 --> 00:04:14.690 align:middle line:84%
is each of those diseases--
cerebral palsy, autism,

00:04:14.690 --> 00:04:18.410 align:middle line:84%
epilepsy-- they all have
their own treatments.

00:04:18.410 --> 00:04:23.520 align:middle line:84%
And all of the treatments
are based on the symptoms.

00:04:23.520 --> 00:04:25.310 align:middle line:84%
And so it's
well-known by science,

00:04:25.310 --> 00:04:28.550 align:middle line:84%
as it has been known for
decades or centuries,

00:04:28.550 --> 00:04:32.990 align:middle line:84%
that you cannot treat the
symptom and make the cause

00:04:32.990 --> 00:04:34.950 align:middle line:90%
or the disease go away.

00:04:34.950 --> 00:04:38.850 align:middle line:84%
This is why physical therapy,
occupational therapy,

00:04:38.850 --> 00:04:42.410 align:middle line:84%
speech therapy, drug
therapy, they cannot work.

00:04:42.410 --> 00:04:45.800 align:middle line:84%
They will not work because
they're attempting to treat

00:04:45.800 --> 00:04:49.050 align:middle line:84%
the symptoms, and
it cannot be done.

00:04:49.050 --> 00:04:51.620 align:middle line:84%
So all the founding
members of The Institutes,

00:04:51.620 --> 00:04:54.230 align:middle line:84%
including my father, who
is a physical therapist,

00:04:54.230 --> 00:04:57.240 align:middle line:84%
had used conventional
therapy with all

00:04:57.240 --> 00:04:59.750 align:middle line:84%
of their hearts
and all their might

00:04:59.750 --> 00:05:01.550 align:middle line:84%
and found that it
wasn't effective.

00:05:01.550 --> 00:05:03.320 align:middle line:84%
And they realized
that if they were

00:05:03.320 --> 00:05:06.950 align:middle line:84%
going to fulfill their
goal, their objective--

00:05:06.950 --> 00:05:09.740 align:middle line:84%
and the objective of The
Institutes from its founding

00:05:09.740 --> 00:05:15.500 align:middle line:84%
was for brain-injured children
to become completely well.

00:05:15.500 --> 00:05:17.900 align:middle line:84%
And the staff had
never seen or heard

00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:21.230 align:middle line:84%
of a brain-injured child
who had ever gotten well.

00:05:21.230 --> 00:05:24.440 align:middle line:84%
So having to treat the brain,
the problem is brain injury.

00:05:24.440 --> 00:05:27.410 align:middle line:84%
And all those children that
I just mentioned to you

00:05:27.410 --> 00:05:28.970 align:middle line:90%
are all brain-injured.

00:05:28.970 --> 00:05:31.410 align:middle line:84%
They all have
neurological problems.

00:05:31.410 --> 00:05:34.580 align:middle line:84%
And yet parents are
distracted and think,

00:05:34.580 --> 00:05:37.130 align:middle line:84%
oh, no, my child is
not brain-injured.

00:05:37.130 --> 00:05:40.310 align:middle line:90%
My child has cerebral palsy.

00:05:40.310 --> 00:05:42.950 align:middle line:84%
We can even go into the
creation of those names,

00:05:42.950 --> 00:05:46.250 align:middle line:90%
because we've seen it happen.

00:05:46.250 --> 00:05:50.150 align:middle line:84%
It's been fascinating and
horrifying at the same time,

00:05:50.150 --> 00:05:52.910 align:middle line:84%
because every year now,
there continue to be

00:05:52.910 --> 00:05:55.400 align:middle line:90%
new names and new diagnoses.

00:05:55.400 --> 00:06:01.310 align:middle line:84%
Now that the genetic tests
have proceeded and are

00:06:01.310 --> 00:06:06.420 align:middle line:84%
so much better now, and they're
discovering new genetic issues,

00:06:06.420 --> 00:06:08.240 align:middle line:90%
and each one gets its own name.

00:06:08.240 --> 00:06:10.760 align:middle line:84%
Smith syndrome,
or Jones syndrome.

00:06:10.760 --> 00:06:15.515 align:middle line:84%
This horrifies the
parents because there

00:06:15.515 --> 00:06:18.740 align:middle line:84%
are only 28 kids with Smith
syndrome in the world.

00:06:18.740 --> 00:06:20.810 align:middle line:90%
This is what parents tell us.

00:06:20.810 --> 00:06:22.055 align:middle line:90%
Their child is one.

00:06:22.055 --> 00:06:23.930 align:middle line:84%
And of course, it means
if there are only 28,

00:06:23.930 --> 00:06:26.360 align:middle line:84%
that nobody knows
anything about them.

00:06:26.360 --> 00:06:29.020 align:middle line:84%
But we were seeing children
with Smith syndrome

00:06:29.020 --> 00:06:32.030 align:middle line:84%
20 years ago, 40 years ago,
before the genetic issue

00:06:32.030 --> 00:06:33.470 align:middle line:90%
was understood.

00:06:33.470 --> 00:06:36.300 align:middle line:84%
And of course, we were getting
results with them as well.

00:06:36.300 --> 00:06:38.660 align:middle line:84%
So now, we have seen
children with every kind

00:06:38.660 --> 00:06:41.930 align:middle line:84%
of genetic issue that has
a neurological component,

00:06:41.930 --> 00:06:46.130 align:middle line:84%
and where the actual
issue is not progressive.

00:06:46.130 --> 00:06:48.430 align:middle line:84%
It's a static brain
injury that has occurred.

00:06:48.430 --> 00:06:51.232 align:middle line:90%
[LIGHT MUSIC]

00:06:51.232 --> 00:06:54.040 align:middle line:90%


00:06:54.040 --> 00:06:56.740 align:middle line:84%
We see the entire spectrum
of brain-injured children,

00:06:56.740 --> 00:06:58.750 align:middle line:84%
from those children
who are mild,

00:06:58.750 --> 00:07:02.740 align:middle line:84%
where their only problem is
they're reading two or three

00:07:02.740 --> 00:07:05.260 align:middle line:90%
years below age level.

00:07:05.260 --> 00:07:09.730 align:middle line:84%
And of course, these children
are considered stupid.

00:07:09.730 --> 00:07:10.995 align:middle line:90%
They're not stupid.

00:07:10.995 --> 00:07:12.370 align:middle line:84%
They have a
neurological problem.

00:07:12.370 --> 00:07:15.120 align:middle line:84%
It can be resolved,
and they can then

00:07:15.120 --> 00:07:17.670 align:middle line:84%
go to the head of
their class or beyond.

00:07:17.670 --> 00:07:19.180 align:middle line:90%
They have that potential.

00:07:19.180 --> 00:07:21.380 align:middle line:84%
And then on the other
end of the spectrum,

00:07:21.380 --> 00:07:24.550 align:middle line:84%
we see children who have been
in a coma, which is the most

00:07:24.550 --> 00:07:26.690 align:middle line:90%
severe form of brain injury.

00:07:26.690 --> 00:07:33.040 align:middle line:84%
So if you're asking what is the
bulk of how children get hurt,

00:07:33.040 --> 00:07:34.960 align:middle line:84%
yes, it's usually
through the process

00:07:34.960 --> 00:07:39.710 align:middle line:84%
of being born, either before
birth or during birth,

00:07:39.710 --> 00:07:43.460 align:middle line:84%
that there is some sort of
trauma in the actual birth

00:07:43.460 --> 00:07:44.260 align:middle line:90%
itself.

00:07:44.260 --> 00:07:46.850 align:middle line:90%
[LIGHT MUSIC]

00:07:46.850 --> 00:07:50.100 align:middle line:90%


00:07:50.100 --> 00:07:54.330 align:middle line:84%
My particular area of expertise
is in terms of mobility.

00:07:54.330 --> 00:07:58.380 align:middle line:84%
And brain-injured children--
typically what the world would

00:07:58.380 --> 00:08:00.600 align:middle line:90%
call cerebral palsy--

00:08:00.600 --> 00:08:03.870 align:middle line:84%
these children have huge
issues in terms of mobility.

00:08:03.870 --> 00:08:05.910 align:middle line:90%
They can come to us immobile.

00:08:05.910 --> 00:08:09.300 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps they're able to crawl
a little bit on their bellies,

00:08:09.300 --> 00:08:14.550 align:middle line:84%
maybe on their hands and knees
creeping, or walking and doing

00:08:14.550 --> 00:08:15.750 align:middle line:90%
so poorly.

00:08:15.750 --> 00:08:21.300 align:middle line:84%
So with these children, there
are a whole series of programs.

00:08:21.300 --> 00:08:24.090 align:middle line:84%
First of all, the
nutritional programs

00:08:24.090 --> 00:08:26.040 align:middle line:84%
are necessary to
give the children

00:08:26.040 --> 00:08:30.330 align:middle line:84%
the energy they need to get
our intensive treatment done.

00:08:30.330 --> 00:08:32.700 align:middle line:84%
So that's an
important component.

00:08:32.700 --> 00:08:36.045 align:middle line:84%
And of course, respiration,
particularly for chil-- well,

00:08:36.045 --> 00:08:39.330 align:middle line:84%
we've found that virtually all
brain-injured children suffer

00:08:39.330 --> 00:08:44.130 align:middle line:84%
from a chronic lack of
oxygenation of the brain,

00:08:44.130 --> 00:08:47.860 align:middle line:84%
and oxygen being the
principal food of the brain.

00:08:47.860 --> 00:08:52.080 align:middle line:84%
If there is that situation,
then all brain functions

00:08:52.080 --> 00:08:54.160 align:middle line:90%
are going to suffer.

00:08:54.160 --> 00:08:56.580 align:middle line:84%
So we put a huge amount
of time and effort

00:08:56.580 --> 00:09:00.090 align:middle line:84%
into the development of
respiratory programs, programs

00:09:00.090 --> 00:09:02.220 align:middle line:90%
that better oxygenate the brain.

00:09:02.220 --> 00:09:06.870 align:middle line:84%
And those programs are necessary
for our physical programs,

00:09:06.870 --> 00:09:09.240 align:middle line:84%
but also for
intellectual programs,

00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:12.090 align:middle line:90%
and to promote health.

00:09:12.090 --> 00:09:14.890 align:middle line:90%
We have a health victory.

00:09:14.890 --> 00:09:18.510 align:middle line:84%
And for a brain-injured child
to have a health victory,

00:09:18.510 --> 00:09:22.290 align:middle line:84%
he or she has to
have had 12 months

00:09:22.290 --> 00:09:26.610 align:middle line:90%
of consecutive perfect health.

00:09:26.610 --> 00:09:34.320 align:middle line:84%
No influenza, no temperature, no
cold, no sniffles, no nothing.

00:09:34.320 --> 00:09:38.100 align:middle line:84%
And these are often children
who may have been hospitalized

00:09:38.100 --> 00:09:42.630 align:middle line:84%
four or five times a year due
to their medical problems,

00:09:42.630 --> 00:09:45.773 align:middle line:84%
and now, 12 months
perfect health.

00:09:45.773 --> 00:09:47.940 align:middle line:84%
And these are two- or
three-year-olds in some cases.

00:09:47.940 --> 00:09:51.060 align:middle line:84%
Well, even average normal
two- or three-year-olds

00:09:51.060 --> 00:09:54.270 align:middle line:84%
can't get away with
that kind of health,

00:09:54.270 --> 00:09:57.970 align:middle line:84%
but with brain-injured
children, it can happen.

00:09:57.970 --> 00:10:01.200 align:middle line:84%
So there's a
respiratory component.

00:10:01.200 --> 00:10:03.420 align:middle line:84%
Of course, there are
areas of the brain that

00:10:03.420 --> 00:10:05.470 align:middle line:90%
are responsible for balance.

00:10:05.470 --> 00:10:08.400 align:middle line:84%
So we have programs for
balanced development.

00:10:08.400 --> 00:10:11.000 align:middle line:84%
There are programs to
develop coordination,

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:14.740 align:middle line:84%
another necessary component
of mobility development.

00:10:14.740 --> 00:10:18.810 align:middle line:84%
So our objective is to get
an immobile child crawling

00:10:18.810 --> 00:10:22.650 align:middle line:84%
on his belly following
the same normal pathway

00:10:22.650 --> 00:10:24.630 align:middle line:90%
that the average baby follows.

00:10:24.630 --> 00:10:29.657 align:middle line:84%
All we're doing is
recreating normal development

00:10:29.657 --> 00:10:30.990 align:middle line:90%
with our brain-injured children.

00:10:30.990 --> 00:10:33.755 align:middle line:84%
So the children learn to
crawl on their bellies

00:10:33.755 --> 00:10:35.130 align:middle line:84%
to the point
they're crawling all

00:10:35.130 --> 00:10:38.640 align:middle line:84%
over the house as a
means of transportation.

00:10:38.640 --> 00:10:41.700 align:middle line:84%
Then we give them a
balanced development program

00:10:41.700 --> 00:10:44.310 align:middle line:84%
so they can push up onto
the third dimension,

00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:46.260 align:middle line:84%
begin to creep on
their hands and knees.

00:10:46.260 --> 00:10:48.960 align:middle line:84%
They do hundreds of
meters of that a day.

00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:52.050 align:middle line:84%
And then there's the process
of learning how to walk

00:10:52.050 --> 00:10:54.030 align:middle line:84%
and becoming
independent walkers,

00:10:54.030 --> 00:10:58.140 align:middle line:84%
and we have a series of programs
for independent walking.

00:10:58.140 --> 00:11:00.960 align:middle line:84%
And then finally, running,
hopping, skipping, and jumping,

00:11:00.960 --> 00:11:04.625 align:middle line:84%
and then on to gymnastics,
biking, swimming.

00:11:04.625 --> 00:11:06.000 align:middle line:84%
And that's when
we're moving them

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:08.760 align:middle line:84%
into physical excellence,
which is our objective

00:11:08.760 --> 00:11:10.620 align:middle line:90%
for every brain-injured child.

00:11:10.620 --> 00:11:15.030 align:middle line:84%
Not to be just average, but
to be physically excellent.

00:11:15.030 --> 00:11:17.808 align:middle line:90%
[LIGHT MUSIC]

00:11:17.808 --> 00:11:21.050 align:middle line:90%


00:11:21.050 --> 00:11:24.100 align:middle line:84%
Well, brain-injured children,
as a symptom of their brain

00:11:24.100 --> 00:11:28.150 align:middle line:84%
injury, are much more
sensitive to certain foods

00:11:28.150 --> 00:11:29.590 align:middle line:90%
than average people.

00:11:29.590 --> 00:11:33.640 align:middle line:84%
So their ability to have
issues in terms of allergy

00:11:33.640 --> 00:11:37.300 align:middle line:84%
is enormous compared to
the average population.

00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:41.620 align:middle line:84%
So our program, of
course, is dairy-free.

00:11:41.620 --> 00:11:44.450 align:middle line:90%
It's gluten-free.

00:11:44.450 --> 00:11:47.140 align:middle line:84%
There are a whole series
of different foods

00:11:47.140 --> 00:11:48.850 align:middle line:90%
that are eliminated.

00:11:48.850 --> 00:11:52.210 align:middle line:84%
And then, with a
rotational diet,

00:11:52.210 --> 00:11:56.410 align:middle line:84%
once the child is desensitized
to that particular kind

00:11:56.410 --> 00:11:59.830 align:middle line:84%
of food, like
citrus, then we will

00:11:59.830 --> 00:12:03.520 align:middle line:84%
begin to rotate in citrus
maybe one or two days

00:12:03.520 --> 00:12:07.180 align:middle line:84%
a week so that they can
have that in their diet,

00:12:07.180 --> 00:12:10.390 align:middle line:84%
but not keep having
it day in and day out.

00:12:10.390 --> 00:12:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And with brain-injured
children, it

00:12:12.130 --> 00:12:14.530 align:middle line:84%
becomes more
difficult and complex,

00:12:14.530 --> 00:12:18.060 align:middle line:84%
particularly the children
that the world calls autistic.

00:12:18.060 --> 00:12:20.740 align:middle line:84%
Now, of course, we disagree
with all of these terms,

00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:23.170 align:middle line:84%
and children who
are autistic are

00:12:23.170 --> 00:12:27.160 align:middle line:84%
injured in the posterior areas
of the midbrain and the cortex.

00:12:27.160 --> 00:12:31.060 align:middle line:84%
And these children often
have very limited diets

00:12:31.060 --> 00:12:34.340 align:middle line:84%
that they have created
for themselves.

00:12:34.340 --> 00:12:36.520 align:middle line:84%
They simply won't
eat other foods,

00:12:36.520 --> 00:12:38.300 align:middle line:84%
making it difficult
for their parents.

00:12:38.300 --> 00:12:42.490 align:middle line:84%
So we have to move beyond
that, because having

00:12:42.490 --> 00:12:44.050 align:middle line:84%
the same foods
all the time, they

00:12:44.050 --> 00:12:46.690 align:middle line:84%
become very sensitive
to those foods,

00:12:46.690 --> 00:12:49.930 align:middle line:84%
and then we need to give them
a much broader range of foods

00:12:49.930 --> 00:12:51.740 align:middle line:90%
that they can eat.

00:12:51.740 --> 00:12:56.680 align:middle line:84%
So in the end, once the parents
have worked this out and we

00:12:56.680 --> 00:13:02.260 align:middle line:84%
have a diet that is tailor-made
for each child in terms of his

00:13:02.260 --> 00:13:05.160 align:middle line:90%
food, his vitamin supplements--

00:13:05.160 --> 00:13:07.960 align:middle line:84%
this is all done with
the medical staff.

00:13:07.960 --> 00:13:13.330 align:middle line:84%
And the work is very advanced
in that all of the children

00:13:13.330 --> 00:13:16.120 align:middle line:84%
receive very
sophisticated blood tests.

00:13:16.120 --> 00:13:17.590 align:middle line:84%
And looking at
these blood tests--

00:13:17.590 --> 00:13:21.490 align:middle line:84%
and we have our own database
where the information about

00:13:21.490 --> 00:13:23.320 align:middle line:90%
each child is put in--

00:13:23.320 --> 00:13:25.900 align:middle line:84%
that information
then can determine

00:13:25.900 --> 00:13:29.530 align:middle line:84%
how we can tailor-make
that nutritional program

00:13:29.530 --> 00:13:32.290 align:middle line:84%
to make sure that all
the elements in the blood

00:13:32.290 --> 00:13:36.090 align:middle line:84%
are at optimum levels
that they should be,

00:13:36.090 --> 00:13:37.840 align:middle line:84%
or that the things
that shouldn't be there

00:13:37.840 --> 00:13:40.580 align:middle line:90%
should be at minimum levels.

00:13:40.580 --> 00:13:46.780 align:middle line:84%
We've now expanded this into a
nutrigenetic test with research

00:13:46.780 --> 00:13:49.330 align:middle line:84%
that we're doing with
Penn State University.

00:13:49.330 --> 00:13:55.630 align:middle line:84%
So now, Penn State has made
available very expensive tests

00:13:55.630 --> 00:13:59.680 align:middle line:84%
for our children at
a very minimal price.

00:13:59.680 --> 00:14:02.950 align:middle line:84%
And so now, our
medical staff can

00:14:02.950 --> 00:14:06.010 align:middle line:84%
look at the genetic
situation of the child,

00:14:06.010 --> 00:14:09.940 align:middle line:84%
look at it together with the
child's digestive situation,

00:14:09.940 --> 00:14:13.210 align:middle line:84%
and then tailor-make
that nutritional program

00:14:13.210 --> 00:14:16.180 align:middle line:90%
even with the genes in mind.

00:14:16.180 --> 00:14:19.360 align:middle line:84%
So this is really
pioneering work.

00:14:19.360 --> 00:14:24.940 align:middle line:84%
And it's ironic that
our relationship

00:14:24.940 --> 00:14:30.220 align:middle line:84%
began with our mutual friendship
with Novak and Jelena Djokovic,

00:14:30.220 --> 00:14:31.930 align:middle line:90%
because here he is.

00:14:31.930 --> 00:14:34.750 align:middle line:84%
He is also having
his blood looked at

00:14:34.750 --> 00:14:38.500 align:middle line:84%
in order to help him to
create the ideal diet so he

00:14:38.500 --> 00:14:40.870 align:middle line:90%
can compete at optimum levels.

00:14:40.870 --> 00:14:44.080 align:middle line:84%
And I haven't talked to him,
but I wouldn't be surprised

00:14:44.080 --> 00:14:48.380 align:middle line:84%
if he's also doing that from
a genetic standpoint as well.

00:14:48.380 --> 00:14:52.720 align:middle line:84%
So here we see top
flight athletes basically

00:14:52.720 --> 00:14:54.880 align:middle line:84%
having the same kind
of nutritional program

00:14:54.880 --> 00:14:57.610 align:middle line:84%
that brain-injured
children need in order

00:14:57.610 --> 00:14:59.440 align:middle line:84%
to have the best
chance of getting well.

00:14:59.440 --> 00:15:02.404 align:middle line:90%
